# Solo Dev Suite — Cursor Rules
# This file tells Cursor how to use the Solo Dev Suite skills.
# Place this file in the project root alongside the skills/ directory.

# ============================================================================
# SUITE OVERVIEW
# ============================================================================
#
# Solo Dev Suite is a collection of 10+ lifecycle skills for solo developers.
# All skills share a central Project Profile stored as JSON files in:
#   skills/solo-dev-suite/profiles/<slug>.json
#
# Skills produce sidecar data files at:
#   skills/solo-dev-suite/profiles/<slug>.<skill-name>.json
#
# Skills are invoked via Python scripts — no external dependencies required.
# All scripts use pure Python stdlib and follow consistent CLI patterns.

# ============================================================================
# SKILL DISCOVERY
# ============================================================================
#
# Available skills and their entry points:
#
# ORCHESTRATOR (start here):
#   python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/profile_io.py --help
#   python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/list_skills.py --help
#   python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/quickstart.py --help
#   python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/dashboard.py --help
#   python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/portfolio.py --help
#   python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/handoff.py --help
#   python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/export_issues.py --help
#   python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/create_skill.py --help
#
# CHILD SKILLS:
#   python skills/adr-generator/scripts/adr_tool.py --help
#   python skills/auto-docs/scripts/docs_tool.py --help
#   python skills/integration-mapper/scripts/integration_tool.py --help
#   python skills/launch-readiness/scripts/readiness_tool.py --help
#   python skills/mvp-scope-guardian/scripts/scope_tool.py --help
#   python skills/saas-pricing-architect/scripts/pricing_tool.py --help
#   python skills/security-audit/scripts/security_tool.py --help
#   python skills/sprint-planner/scripts/sprint_tool.py --help
#   python skills/tech-debt-register/scripts/debt_tool.py --help
#   python skills/testing-strategy/scripts/testing_tool.py --help

# ============================================================================
# RULES
# ============================================================================

# Rule: When the user asks about project scope, features, or MVP decisions
# Action: Use the MVP Scope Guardian
# Command: python skills/mvp-scope-guardian/scripts/scope_tool.py
# Phases: scope

# Rule: When the user asks about pricing, tiers, or monetization
# Action: Use the SaaS Pricing Architect
# Command: python skills/saas-pricing-architect/scripts/pricing_tool.py
# Phases: scope, grow

# Rule: When the user asks about architecture decisions or ADRs
# Action: Use the ADR Generator
# Command: python skills/adr-generator/scripts/adr_tool.py
# Phases: architecture, build

# Rule: When the user asks about third-party services, dependencies, or integrations
# Action: Use the Integration Mapper
# Command: python skills/integration-mapper/scripts/integration_tool.py
# Phases: architecture, build

# Rule: When the user asks about sprints, velocity, or task planning
# Action: Use the Sprint Planner
# Command: python skills/sprint-planner/scripts/sprint_tool.py
# Phases: build

# Rule: When the user asks about tech debt or code quality debt
# Action: Use the Tech Debt Register
# Command: python skills/tech-debt-register/scripts/debt_tool.py
# Phases: build, sustain

# Rule: When the user asks about testing strategy or test coverage
# Action: Use the Testing Strategy skill
# Command: python skills/testing-strategy/scripts/testing_tool.py
# Phases: build

# Rule: When the user asks about security, vulnerabilities, or pre-ship security
# Action: Use the Security Audit
# Command: python skills/security-audit/scripts/security_tool.py
# Phases: ship

# Rule: When the user asks about launch readiness or go-live checklist
# Action: Use the Launch Readiness skill
# Command: python skills/launch-readiness/scripts/readiness_tool.py
# Phases: ship

# Rule: When the user asks about documentation, README, or changelog
# Action: Use the Auto-Docs skill
# Command: python skills/auto-docs/scripts/docs_tool.py
# Phases: ship, sustain

# Rule: When the user asks to see project status or dashboard
# Action: Use the Dashboard
# Command: python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/dashboard.py status <slug>

# Rule: When the user asks to compare projects or see portfolio health
# Action: Use the Portfolio view
# Command: python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/portfolio.py view

# Rule: When the user asks to export items to an issue tracker
# Action: Use the Issue Tracker Export
# Command: python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/export_issues.py export <slug> --help

# ============================================================================
# WORKFLOW
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. FIRST TIME: Create a project profile
#    python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/quickstart.py detect <project-path>
#    # Then use profile_io.py init to create the profile with detected + manual fields
#
# 2. CHECK PHASE: See what skills apply
#    python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/list_skills.py --slug <slug>
#
# 3. RUN A SKILL: Each skill reads the profile automatically
#    python skills/<skill-name>/scripts/<tool>.py <command> <slug>
#
# 4. VIEW STATUS: See all skill outputs in one place
#    python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/dashboard.py status <slug>
#
# 5. RECORD THE RUN: Update the profile's last_skill_run timestamp
#    echo '{"last_skill_run": {"<skill-name>": "<ISO-date>"}}' | \
#      python skills/solo-dev-suite/scripts/profile_io.py update <slug> --from-stdin

# ============================================================================
# CONVENTIONS
# ============================================================================
#
# - All scripts accept --help for usage information
# - All scripts accept --json for machine-readable output where applicable
# - Exit code 0 = success, 1 = not found, 2 = broken install
# - Profile slugs are kebab-case identifiers (e.g., "my-saas-app")
# - Sidecar files follow the pattern: <slug>.<skill-name>.json
# - All scripts use UTF-8 encoding
# - No external Python dependencies — pure stdlib only
